\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5506367 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 Could I have your name?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7226846 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 Gwendoline Mary Whitelam.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5506367 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 And your present address?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7226846 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14421629\charrsid2636949 18 B}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 road Street, Port Talbot.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5506367 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 And you are a widow?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7226846 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 Widow.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5506367 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 The year of your marriage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7226846 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 1924, July, 6th, 1924.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5506367 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 And your year of birth?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7226846 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 1899.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5506367 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 Where were you born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7226846 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 I was born in West End, Taibach, Port Talbot.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5506367 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 How many years did you live in the house where you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7226846 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 
About two years I should imagine, I have a very faint memory of West End, because we moved up to Park Street, from there, because we wanted more room, the family was growing with b
oys, mother wanted - father wanted more bedrooms you see. So we moved up to - Park Street which had more bedrooms.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5506367 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 So you moved there in about 1901?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7226846 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 That's it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5506367 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 Where did you go from there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7226846 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 To a - a Street called Park Street.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5506367 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 In Taibach?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7226846 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 Taibach, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5506367 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 Then from Park Street?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7226846 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 To Broad Street, where I live now, which I've lived in for sixty-two years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5506367 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 Why did you move from Park Street to Broad Street?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7226846 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 Because - it didn't have the - convenient facilities th
at we have here, bathroom and - indoor toilet, everything at the back and bigger bedrooms, which was very essential for us as we were a - large family. But we - oh - will I give them the names that are down here, aren't they full names?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5506367 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 How many brothers and sisters did you have?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7226846 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 Four brothers, three sisters.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5506367 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 If you could remember the birth order?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7226846 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 
Yes. The elder brother was called David Hopkin Daviks, and he was born 1882. Then William Daviks 1886. Elizabeth Ann Daviks 1889. Idris Daviks 1892. Brynly Daviks 1897. Gwendoline Mary, myself, 1899. Blodwen Daviks 1904.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5506367 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 How old was your father when you were born? He was thirty}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14421629\charrsid2636949  }{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 nine wasn't he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7226846 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 YES.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5506367 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 Where did he come from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7226846 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 Originally - his - people - they were people from Llangranog, Cardiganshire. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5506367 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 Did he come from there himself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7226846 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 
No, I think he was born here, in Taibach. A place they call Short Lake, down the other - where the dock - the float, we used to call the float near the docks.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5506367 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 But the family came from Cardiganshire?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7226846 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 Cardiganshire, from Llandrodnod, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5506367 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 What was his occupation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7226846 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 A tin worker. He was - a - in the end a shearer, he - a - a roller}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14421629\charrsid2636949 -}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 man in the first place, and then you}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14421629\charrsid2636949 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 d go from the roller}
{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14421629\charrsid2636949 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 man to the shearer and that was the highest peak in the tin works at that time.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5506367 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 Did he start off as a boy in the tin works?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7226846 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 
Yes, as a small boy, he started off as a small boy in the tin works. They called them bundlers. Bundlers, yes. They used to bundle the pieces of tin - which were cut off \{BLANK\}
 with shears, by - by the shearer. And they'd bundle these and take them away in a little sort of trolley, see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5506367 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 And then he progressed did he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7226846 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 He progressed up there from the bundler up to the shearer, which was the top job.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5506367 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 He spent his whole life in that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7226846 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 Whole life in the tin works, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5506367 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 He didn't have another job at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7226846 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 No. No. He didn't have another job, that was - that was his only job.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5506367 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 Did he have any casual or part time jobs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7226846 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 
No, he was very fond of gardening, his father was a gardener. He was very very fond of gardening, and he delighted in it and he was very very fine gardener too, he could always grow everything beautifully.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5506367 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 He didn't do a part time job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7226846 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5506367 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 Do you remember your father ever being out of work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7226846 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 
Yes. For two years - he was completely out of work in - in this work, the - the - owners went bankrupt, and they were out for two years, and it was a time when there was no dole or anything else
, and mother has us - we children and - she used to say - how she used to always cook a nice meal for us, warm meal just the same, and - and I can remember once - in a - in the train, a person asking her, you - he seemed to be a type of a communistic type
 
you know, with some sol - soldiers and military people in the - in the compartment, and she had a coat with a nice fur collar, and he thought she looked like a capitalist, and he said, have - he was inciting these young men to brush her or rush her - or R
ussian or something you see. So - a lady who was there, Mrs}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14364464\charrsid2636949 .}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 
 Jenkins, she said - this man was very very active with these boys, trying to incite them and get them into the communistic belief. So she said }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14364464\charrsid2636949 \endash }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
