ht out, she said, I can remember my husband out of work for two years he had no job, and how - he said, how did you live then? Oh she said, I tapped their shoes, I looked after the children every way and never went in debt. Well, he said, how did you mana
ge that? I had a very good father who could lend me some money, I paid it back, and, she said, I've been very thrifty in my time and - I cooked the meals properly and gave them good food the whole time, and I kept them very very respectably. So I -
