a big dolly tub with all the clothes, and she had two days washing. My father working in the works of course and my - my elder brother, he - he was working in this - in the - in the works too. She had the heavy flannels, Welsh people wore Welsh flannels i
n
 those days of course, she had the dolly and what we called a rubbing board, they'd rub - one day for the heavies, for the underclothes, and another day for the whites, and the boys in these days, they used to wear caps and - vests, slips and also girls e
m
broideries and it was a full time job, there was no - dressing up - at - after lunch to go out, because - the ironing took a bit of doing, with a - with a family of seven as we were, and - she enjoyed - no, she had no help at all. She'd do it all herself.
 She was - yes, she used to love it.
