, because of course when we'd have our anniversary services it was quite a - a turn out, and like - I can always remember the - the Elders of the church and they'd - they'd come on the anniversary and they'd top hats and frock coats you see. That was the 
d
ay of the year, yes, for the - for the - was the anniversary in the church, and everybody - we had a - a saying in Welsh that I'm very very fond of - everybody will be in - in decept parr, meaning, our respectable clothes, and they were always kept for Su
nday for the services - on Sunday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5506367 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 How often would you have new clothes?
