Oh we never - we - we - well she - mother - Monday morning was a big day - of brushing all the suits because of course we didn't have macadam on the streets then, it was mud
 and the dust, brushing and the turn up trousers, she'd open those all, she'd brush all those suits, fold them, put them by for the following Sunday, and our clothes the same. And we weren't allowed to wear the same clothes for Sunday school as we wore fo
r Sunday to go to church. Oh no, we had to have the best, we - we were - we had the best to go to the services, but for Sunday school, we changed for Sunday school. Always changed.
