Yes, I can remember in West End - my mother saying whilst we were in West End, if she - we - they'd go in turns when the - we children were very young, they'd go 
in turns to church in the morning, my mother would go one Sunday he'd go another and he'd cook a beautiful dinner, he was an expert cook, and he was wonderful, we used to have the brass stand and the brass fender, and the gongs and the pokers, my grandfat
her, being an engineer and made those himself you see, and the brass rod along, along the mantle - piece, and - oh he was an expert at cleaning brasses. He'd clean the brasses, always clean brasses. Always clean brasses, every week.
