ome out of the bedroom, and we used to have - we Welsh people were very fond in those days of - a basin of sop in the morning, see. It was made of bread - and that was - sugared, with tea poured over it, and a lump of butter on the top and that was spread
 
around, and then a piece of cheese with that. And I can remember my brothers always talking about my father, he'd make a different animal in the cheese, they'd have a slice of cheese, and he'd make different animals, a cat or a rabbit or something, every 
morning to amuse - he was - he was very very fond of the children, yes, he would do that sort of thing. Yes. He was a very lovable man.
