, he loved the sea. And he nearly ran away to sea when he was a boy, they caught him in time, on Miss Talbot's yacht in the Lynx, they caught him in time, he was going to run away to sea, loved the sea and he loved taking me down - every Saturday afternoo
n
 to the docks which was full at that time of sailing ships, and he'd be describing the different ships to me and we'd go to the lock gates and we'd watch them - the pilots bringing in the ships and - oh I used to be thrilled, that was the annual - the wee
kly trip then, down to the docks.
