be full of food and these bottles of small beer which they - herb - herb beer that they'd make at home, my mother was an expert at that, and - my father take a bottle of it to work with him, and you'd see the cork; shooting off on the way down, on these -
 on this bottle of small beer, oh they were great days they were. They - we don't have that fun today, it's too ready made today.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5506367 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 Would your father look after you when your mother was out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7226846 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 Oh yes. Yes. Always looked after us. And - put - he'd - h
e'd - if - if she had to go out in the night he'd take us to bed of course you see.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5506367 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 Would he do everything for you then, bath you then and undress you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7226846 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 Yes, he'd undress -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5506367 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 He'd put you to bed, would he say prayers with you or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7226846 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 Well - well, yes, he - he would - we had to say our prayers every night of course.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5506367 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 He would do everything for you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7226846 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 Yes. Oh yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5506367 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 Did you have any take that you had to carry out regularly at home to help your mother and father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7226846 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 
Oh yes, we all had our jobs, set jobs to do. My mother was a great believer in good manners, organisation, method, method was a big word, she had that written up in the scullery, method. When she'd cook everything thing was back as she was using 
it, there was to be no mess on the table or anything else, I never saw such a tidy person, she was an excellent cook, and it was always - the method and good manners very very keen - on bringing us up that way. And - that was drilled into us very very - v
ery very young.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5506367 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 What sort of jobs would you have to do when you were a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7226846 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 
Oh - tudy up, dust our bedrooms - we - we had to clean our own bedroom, and - wash the front, scrub that. Oh each one of us had our jobs. And we'd - we'd iron occasiona
lly, if it wasn't anything that was very very frilly or with fripperies you know, she liked to do that and she had a wonderful way with goffering you see. We had all these lovely embroideries and - she - she was - I can see here now, how she'd goffer thes
e beautiful embroideries after she'd iron it and - to bring it out frilly you know. Oh yes, we all had our jobs to do.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5506367 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 What did you have to do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7226846 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 I usually washed the front. Our boys were put to - sweep the back with a - with a heavy broom - with a
 heavy brush you know, and my sister and my eldest sister, she'd mostly do - the - sewing and - any general work that was going around you know, she was very - she was very very good girl. Wonderful at embroidering. Very clever with drawn thread work. Bea
utiful linen drawn thread work, we'd go to Ben Evans to buy the linen, Swansea. And of course her bottom drawer was all that you see, I think \{BLANK\} has got most of it there now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5506367 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 Would she make her own things for the bottom drawer?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7226846 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 Clothes? Oh everything. Oh yes, everything. And bought for the bottom drawer, there was that tea}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2100535\charrsid2636949 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 set up there now, that was bought for my bottom drawer - my mother -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5506367 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 When would that have been bought?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7226846 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 Oh long - years before you married. I remember mother, we
 had a bazaar in our church I remember my mother buy - bringing home a lovely eiderdown quilt for me, I - I wouldn't have been more than sixteen, I - I - I wasn't courting at that time. A beautiful eiderdown quilt, she bought it on a stall at the bazaar s
he fancied it so much and I had it of course for years after I was married. Beautiful pale blue with a pink paisley centre to it, I can remember it, lovely quilt.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5506367 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 Would Liz have started making things for her bottom drawer before she was courting?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7226846 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 Oh dear, yes. Always. We were trained to start young, to make a bottom drawer. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5506367 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 You would collect things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7226846 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 Oh absolutely, yes. I've got - I've got heaps of linen now that I had then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5506367 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 What about your brothers, what would Dai have to do, what was his job, did they have any particular jobs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7226846 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 Yes, he was very fond of - of - cleaning the cutlery, he was. With Will, they two would clean the cutlery.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5506367 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 And Idris?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7226846 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 I don't remember Idris doing very much of anything really. He was a 
real gentleman. Isn't it funny? He was the gentleman of the family, and always immaculate in dress you see. I think that's why he went to the outfitters, he went as an apprentice the outfitters - business around - my father and mother opened a business fo
r him, outfitting business in Station Road.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5506367 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 What about Bryn?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7226846 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 Oh a big sportsman Bryn was. Very fond of rugby.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5506367 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 You don't remember him having a job to do around the house regularly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7226846 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 Oh yes, he had - he had }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2100535\charrsid2636949 to do his - he had to do the ti}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 
dying up, the sweeping or - go errands you know, on a bike. And he - but he was very very clever with - with hockey as a boy, and he - he was a terrible tease. But you know he was a sleepwalker, he'd get up, I can always remember that, he'd get up, he'd d
r
ess, very active mind, and - the doctors told Idris don't you disturb him or - or - or - or shake him, you just follow him and talk him out of it. Remember when we had the car he'd go under the car - screw a few nuts and brother Idris would say, what are 
y
ou doing Bryn? Oh, he said, there's something loose here under this car, it wants seeing to so I'm screwing up a few of these nuts here, and he'd - he'd go on his way to Station Road and my brother'd have to follow him. Very very active, but a - a love - 
oh, a music, loved music.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5506367 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 What about Blod, would she have had a job around the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7226846 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 
Oh yes, she - she was more active than I was, she'd turn out the upstairs, on - on - on say a Thursday afternoon now when the shop was closed and she - before she - she went - as a clerk.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5506367 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 How about when you were children in school, would you have jobs then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7226846 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 
No - yes, oh we were all - kept going, we weren't allowed to sit idle, or we'd have to have a hobby, we'd have to do something. You see, and singing, we were very musical family you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5506367 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 Did the older children help the younger with things they found difficult?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7226846 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5506367 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 Like dressing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7226846 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 Oh yes. I'll tell you what now. Mother always prided herself that we were such a happy close fam
ily - she - the - the great boast she always made was she never saw one rise a hand in anger to the other, and of course I - that was due to her. My father being quiet you see, we'd be all on the table perhaps on a Sunday and - all of us together on Sunda
y
, and perhaps the argument would go - little bit heated. All mother had to raise a forefinger or open her eyes wide, dyna ddigon, that's enough, and we knew, we had to stop it. And I think she always - avoided the - the argument getting to a heated argume
nt, and - she - that was her greatest boast at the end of her days, that she never saw one raise a hand in anger to the other.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5506367 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 Would you have to help the younger ones, would you have had to help Blod?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7226846 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 Oh yes, I - and take her out in a pram and that sort of thing. We - we'd all do that mind, help each other in that way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5506367 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 Were you expected to go go bed at a certain time when you were at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7226846 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 Oh yes. Yes. We'd - have regular hours. As I tell you, mother would go with us to bed in the night.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5506367 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 Do you remember what time you went?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7226846 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 
Oh - never later than about - seven or eight - eight, unless we were going to this church meeting, the - it would be eight o'clock that night or half past eight. But of course the children were allowed to
 go out earlier you see than the elders then, after they'd say their verses we were allowed to go home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5506367 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 Would you go home on your own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7226846 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 Yes. We'd go on our own. And - if - mother perhaps would come later on, she would go out a bit earlier from th
e service, my father remain in. And she'd come to put us - she'd always put us to bed, never failed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5506367 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 Always your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7226846 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 Always.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5506367 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 No one else?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7226846 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5506367 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 At what age did you put yourself to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7226846 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 Oh - what would I be, 'cos I slept w
ith my eldest sister, Liz. We slept together. About - so I wasn't really going to bed alone until she married of course you see. Oh - say about twelve or -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5506367 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 When would your mother stop coming up and putting you to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7226846 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 Oh when we were - round about ten - twelve, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5506367 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 You shared the bedroom with Liz?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7226846 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5506367 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 And anyone else?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7226846 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 No. Just Liz and I.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5506367 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 Did you share the bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7226846 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 Oh yes, the same bed, double bed you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5506367 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 What about the boys?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7226846 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 Well they were in the m
iddle bedroom which was big room, two double beds there for the boys. And then - when - when Blod was very young of course she was in a cot of her own in the front - in a - sort of a little - a - a bedroom that they'd - put - taken out of the front bedroo
m, they'd made a partition - for her in the front bedroom - it was a big bedroom.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5506367 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 Your father and mother would be in the front bedroom?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7226846 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 That's right, yes, that's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5506367 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 The boys would be in the middle bedroom and you and Liz at the back?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7226846 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 That's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5506367 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 Dai would sleep with Will?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7226846 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 That's right. And Bryn with Idris you see. Yes, that's how it was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5506367 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 What about bathing, what room would you bath in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7226846 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 Oh - out in the scullery as a rule and lock the door and no one was allowed in - in different - that's }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2100535\charrsid2636949 h}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 ow they came over her after so many - seven years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5506367 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 How did you bath?
