\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7226846 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 Oh well, 
after the bath. I can always remember on Christmas Eve, it's very vivid in my memory now - we were always - there was always a new nightdress for Christmas Eve. S- that Father Christmas would see us in our new nightdresses, and we looked forward to that. 
B
ut it was very funny, I - I - I - the one thing I wish - I regret I hadn't asked my mother - we'd hung our stocking up of course, was nothing like the presents they have here these days, it was an apple, an orange, a sugar mouse or a sugar pig - a bar of 
chocolate, packet of sweets or something fancy in sweets, but at the bottom of the stocking were always cinders, and I all - and I wish I'd asked her - what was - if there was some object in those cinders. I wonder what it was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5506367 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 You hung your stocking up at the bottom of the bed?
