\insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 en?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7226846 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2100535\charrsid2636949 Hallowe}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 en, yes, yes. Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5506367 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 What did you used to do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7226846 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 We never - we never - in Taibach had it - on cords, lots of people put
 the apples on cord now, but it - they were - the apples were put in - the big bath - on the hearth you see, and then we'd be on our knees then trying the - get the stems and the - the big - bigger brothers at the back were pushing our heads down you see,
 and there was, - hllyballoo. Oh there was - there was some screaming you know. 'Cos - we didn't like the water very much, I suppose, and they weren't very very - gentle about it, they were pretty rough believe me. Oh we had a whale of a time then.
