ul thing. But I couldn't find the crane, that it was a hanging on you see. So it was - the cooking, and a Dutch oven we used to have. Where she used to make Welsh cakes in the Dutch oven. In front of the fire. Put a little stand you see to stand and - you
 turned it different sides, there - there was a - a sort of a cover to it. And you'd turn it for each side to cook properly, the Welsh cakes were put at the bottom of this and you'd turn the cover both sides.
