rm - a hot dinner. Oh yes. And two big dishes of rice pudding. 'Cos our boys loved - and two huge enamel dishes of - every day, and prunes. And then - every day, like the clock. Mother was very fond of cooking. Nothing tinned, no tins, oh no, it ha
d to be good wholesome food. And she was very fond of what we used to say, gwyly Pasc, pastie gwyl, a meat pie. She'd make a big enamel dish of shin beef, onions, and it was delicious, believe me, 'cos she was wonderful at pastry, you know, the pastry, gw
yl you Pasc we used to call it you see.
