\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5506367 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 Was your mother an easy person to talk to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7226846 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 Very. Very amusing, you'd never be bored with her. Even to the last - oh well -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5506367 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 What about children, when you were youngsters in school? Was your mother easy to talk to then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7226846 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 
Oh yes, always. Very amusing person, and loved children. And there's nothing she delighted in more than watching the school children - now you know going to school, we lived so near the school, and she thought what advantages they were having toda
y to her time. Walking - four miles going to Tremain school from Carmarthen, each way across Pontbettysea and - and today from - from bus - to the - to the school, from school home to the door. But you know I - I've got the feeling is that they'll never m
a
ke the characters that our parents made. Because they've not been sacrifice - they don't know what sacrifice is. There's something in a sacrifice you know. Things I'm a - I think are much to the advantage and I'm very proud of the advantages we've gained 
i
n Wales and everywhere else today, but I think there's a lot to be said about a sacrifice. If you don't sacrifice character isn't made, because I think character's made - in - on the heart too, it's one of the finest universities in the world I think. It'
s as your character's made and I don't think that people today will make the characters that the old people were because they haven't sacrificed. And in sacrifice a character is made I think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5506367 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 Did your mother show you affection?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7226846 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 Oh great affection
. Great affection. And a wonderful person if you were ill. Always consoled you. But could be very witty too. Now my father would - was troubled sometimes with kidney trouble you see, and he'd sit in a corner, and I can remember one day, she called me over
 
and she said - 'cos I'd never left home, and he was sitting in a corner with a stick in his hand, and she said - Gwen, come here. Have you ever seen a sick man sitting down with a stick in his hand? I always thought a stick was to help you to walk. And - 
f
ather - father - my father turned daggers you know, he thought this was very insulting. Well, he said, he was feeling so ill I don't think I shall recover this attack. So she called me back now from the kitchenette again, she said, Gwen - you'd better go 
o
ut and buy a suit of mourning. You're father's just announced his funeral. This is the sixth, she said, this year. Now, she said, you shall have a funeral, and I'll see it'll be a very respectable one. So don't be greedy. Sit down and be quite. You'll get
 over it all right, and - of course he'd have to laugh. She was very - she'd always have you out of any trouble, she had a way - of - she'd such a bright nature, and a - and was wonderful with sick people.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5506367 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 When you said you were consoled when you were not well, in which way, would she cuddle you?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7226846 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 
Yes, she would. And she'd - save any bright cheerful things to you. She'd say to me, because I - I had very bad chest trouble and asthma and different things, and - she'd come down in the morning after I
 was up of course and - she'd say, well - how are you today? Always bright and breezy. Oh, I'd say, all right. Oh can't you find some complaint, surely there's something wrong? She'd always shake you out - of whatever was wrong with you, she had that - sh
