Well - she'd - change us for the night attire, in our night attire, you see, then she'd put - comfortable clothes around us and a - and a shawl and a wrap, then a big shawl which we called a Welsh - Welsh shawl, and that was wrapped
 around the child and the mother, what we call in Welsh fashion, and - not just wrapped around the child, it was wrapped around the shoulders of the mother and tucked into the child and brought round with the other arm, you see.
