 on the Taibach Bridge, Prudrith Bridge, our Sunday school. And then I can remember one day it was raining pouring, and mother had a big cloak, it was from this aunt in the Rhondda she'd been with, and she called it Clogyn Auntie Cathryn, Auntie Cathryn's
