\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5506367 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 What other social activities organised by the chapel did you take part in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7226846 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 Oh, the choir would have a social - a big social - always - in the vestry. After a performance especially whe
n we'd do one of our big performances - they - they'd always arrange a big social - and - and a - quite a big night in the vestry. Beautiful sit down supper of course - meat - pickles, all sorts of stuff. Beautiful trifles, cakes, everybody would bring so
m
ething. I can remember my mother - she would bake - with - she'd buy with Watkins the butcher, and they'd always press her a beautiful tongue. And she always bought a tongue for the - and that was usually kept 'til the last, for the table servers - to hav
e
 in the end. They were - they were having a special sit down tea they would you see. And some would bring a joint, a let of lamb or - oh it was quite a do, we used - and then we'd have a - a lovely entertainment, we had so much talent in our church at tha
t
 time you see. So many could sing, soloists, reciters and male voice parties I tell you, and little quartets, duets, oh it was really a talented church. Well it was looked up to and of course it - Dyffryn was the oldest church - ever - 'cos it started in 
1
764, after the Revival of Howell Harris, in - when he came to preach in Aberafon - this - Evan Thomas and the Dyffryn Parm, happened here, but he - he was disgusted with the reception he had in Aberafon, he - shook the dust from his feet and said he'd nev
e
r go back there again. And then in - in a few years afterwards this Evan Thomas - started this church in a barn, it was - it was there before the Holy Cross church was even - it was the first religious building - 'cos they worshipped there for six years a
nd of course it carried on and it was a - a very very talented church. Very strong church. Oh I've got very wonderful memories - and it's very pathetic to see it now, going down and the times that we can remember.
