Oh - when he wasn't working in the night some - always on a Sunday night. We'd have this family prayer. After church, when we were all home after church service.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5506367 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 What would happen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7226846 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 
Well - as I tell you this big Bible would come out, my father would commence first, with a prayer. And we'd - he'd read - he'd read a chapter and my mother then would give us our verses for the weeknight service as I tell 
you - that we were supposed to learn, she'd choose a verse for us on Sunday that we were supposed to learn for the Wednesday service.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5506367 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 Did your father take an interest in politics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7226846 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 Not - very - a big Liberal my father was. He wasn't - a - no, not
 a very - wild politician at all, a very quite, you know, in a - a very genuine sincere man, believed in what - in - in his policies and what he - he believed in. My mother was more fond of politics. More interested.
