\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7226846 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 Well I think because - they all fe
lt you know, the chapel people all felt it was a - it was their duty to vote a Liberal because - they were mostly religious people. Who were in the Liberal association at that time. The politicians in the Liberals were mostly chapel people then, non - con
f
ormist people, particularly in Wales you see. Because - Mabonne, he was a big Liberal, he was the M.P. for - Merthyr Tydfil I think it was wasn't it, and of course he was brought up in Carmarthen, and my mother would remember his mother very well, she kep
t
