Oh yes. Quite the thing. And the Liberals had red - red rosettes then, and the Kories blue you see. And I remember Preston, Taibach, he was a big Tory, he had a - and he had grocers shop in Taibach. And - he was a big Tor
y you see and he'd have a big rosette, and he'd have a dog running through Taibach with a big blue rosette. So somebody tied a kettle on his ta}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8061432\charrsid2636949 i}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 l one day, running through Taibach with this kettle tied to his tail with the big blue rosette so I don't think 
Mr Preston put a rosette on his dog after that. Oh it was very warm - procession, and they used to sing, vote, vote, vote for - Brydwell Jones was our M.P., I remember that well, remember we children going round - with the placards. Push your - oh big Lib
