Oh be - the day of the election. Oh the day of the election the parade was. Oh we'd have a whale of a time. Great time we'd have. Marching round the streets. Shouting for our man you know, of course our parents were telling us who t
o shout for. But there were very few Conservatives. Because I think - we were mostly non-conformists, really church people, like the owners of the works and that would be voting Conservative, but all the chapel people and non-conformers would vote Liberal
 mostly. It was all Liberal then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5506367 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 But grown ups wouldn't go round, would the Tories have a procession?
