Oh - mostly in the church or out walking, they'd go for walks. And they'd go - visit friends, because it was very very neighbourly place, very - 
friendly place Taibach was, you had so many friends. And a big saying with my mother was to be rich in friends was to be rich indeed. She was very friendly woman herself and my father was shyer, but very friendly and a nice - a very gentle type of man. An
d
 - they would all do good turns for each other, and they'd go round visiting the sick. They were very good in Tiabach that way. If there were anybody sick, particularly somebody that in the church, they were very good sick visitors, my father and mother d
