d a lot of that, round to the sick of the church, and took - perhaps - give the - the sermon of the previous Sunday or the Gamanfa ganu and - my mother would sing some of the hymns of the Gamanfa Ganu to the people that were too sick to come you see. That
 
sort of thing. Oh they were very very good sick visitors, they were noted for that. And my father was a - a very sincere humble man. When he'd take part in prayer meeting now he was - beautiful on prayer, he'd always weep, he was never good enough, and ev
