rybody else would weep. They always said they loved to hear my father take part because - there was something so very humble and sincere in his prayer you see. And we were brought up on that, but a very straight man mind. Could - couldn't stand hypocrites
.
 Because if anybody had said anything hypocritical in the church meeting - which he said quite the reverse perhaps in the park in the afternoon, or talking in the park as the - members would, and they would say something quite the reverse to what they'd s
