ck and white beaded collar on the black frock and white gloves for the concert. And she was very popular in Carmarthen, and - they would shout out - some of the crowd, a gang of boys you know, who - who were - were very fond of my mother, she was very you
n
g then of course, she wasn't married - well done, encore, Eos - Eos - Hopcyn Davies engineer. See? The - Fronffraith then Hopcyn Davies, the blackbird, well done Hpcyn Davis's blackbird, and that's the greatest honour she felt that she was allowed to sing
 - on her own - with Eos Morlais, to her - that was a very great honour in a concert, to be chosen, he was - the crack singer of those days.
