 was a concert in Taibach now she - she'd be chosen. That's why they called her Mary Davis the singer you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5506367 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 Did she ever go out to enjoy herself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7226846 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 Well, yes, but - she was a person who always liked to take her family with her you see. And had 
to be somewhere - oh - well the first time now father was very - much narrower than my mother, he couldn't stand cinemas or theatres, you see. And - my mother loved - opera as I tell you you see. Well the - a - Turners Opera - Opera Company came here to t
h
e New Theatre and - my brother, elder brother, was so fond of music wanted her to see Faust. To show how the devil was tempting man you see. So - she'd never been to an opera before, that's the first opera she ever heard, and the first time the operas cam
e
 to Port Talbot anyway. So he booked seats for to go now, and told my father now that the boys wanted her to go to hear this wonderful singing, these great - artists, and it was called the Moody - not the Moody Manners, the Turner Opera Company was the fi
r
st that came, Moody Manners was second. And - Mary, he said, you're taking the first step downhill. Now, he said, you're going to put the children on the road to destruction. Well, she said, it appears such a wonderful opera, and Verdi, one of our greates
t
 composers had composed this opera, and it's about the devil tempting man, the downfall of man, but how this soprane - conquered the devil - who tried to entice her too down. So David Hopcyn tellms me, she said, and we're all going - I'm - I'd love to hea
r and see these great singers and this great - this great opera. Oh, well my father was very annoyed. And my mother used to love to go to things like that. Concerts.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5506367 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 Did she go to the opera after that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7226846 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 Oh dear, yes, she went -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5506367 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 What did your father say?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7226846 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 
Well he was very disgusted, he was turning daggers and didn't relish it at all. So - and when I first went with my husband, he was musical director of a cinema, cinemas were terrible places, terrible the work of the devil, and - Blod was 
going with a publican's son, we teenagers now. Mary - and we'd been courting on the sly my husband and I for a month - for a - for a twelve month. What's this I hear, he said, about our Gwen? Going with an old showman? And our Blod going with a publican's
 
son, Mary, the roof will come down on our heads, it must be put a stop to, he said. But - and yet, he - he asked us now what do we see in these young men. What do you see in that showman, he said. He looks like a foreigner. 'Cos he was always very fair an
d
 he used to wear a big sombrero hat and - coat with the astrakhan collar. Well character I see in him daddy, I said, he's a man of very strong character, and in - in the shopping business I had handled all sorts of men, I've handled men in opera, because 
-
 our local operatic society, and that's where you test men, I said, in the opera or in drama I said. But I've found out that this man is a very strong character, and I like his character. What do you see in that publican's son, said he to Blod now. A gent
l
eman daddy, she said, I've handled all sorts of men - so she was so popular in the opera of course singing the lead, and she had plenty of boy friends, I see a gentleman in Billy Joe - but do you know to his dying breath he said, these girls knew what the
y were doing, they made heaven on earth for us, those two young men.
