ghbour, she'd go for a little trip to Cardiff for the neighbours you know to do some shopping, or Swansea, but she wasn't very much for going out in the - in the nights, just to service and chapel or a good - if there was a - something good on, 'cos pictu
r
es weren't very popular at that time, but she would go and see a good film mind. And a good play. Go to the New Theatre. And - go to any good - good - amusing play, a comedy she liked. Loved comedy. Not so much - she didn't like these horrors at all. Didn
't enjoy them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5506367 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 You say she'd go to a play, would it be in Port Talbot?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7226846 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 Yes, in the New Theatre. In the New Theatre in Port Talbot. I remember -
