i
s baby had been born to my mother because I had been a delicate child, I'd been pampered rather. So the morning she was born, it was in January and it was snowing. And the cradle was ready there all dolled up and of course in those days the beds were done
 
beautifully with white muslin and pink bows and - oh and the dressing table was decorated with this beautiful - muslin and bows all over the place you see. And - I - when I got into the bedroom and my mother showed me this little baby I was - and it was s
