ch a cold day she wouldn't put it in the cradle, she kept it alongside her in the bed with here and of course I didn't want to look at that thing, I wanted my mother to make a fuss of me, I was one side I said, push here the other side. And I can remember
 
Uncle coming down, I was so jealous of this baby, and he said - he said, hand he - he realized I was very jealous of this child, so he said, don't worry, he said, I'll take her back, he said, to Carmarthen, they were living in Carmarthen, I've got a bonne
