s and - oh - my sister's pals, there about twenty of them come from the Sunday morning chapel to see this baby now you see. So - I can remember one of them giving me jelly jubes, black and red, you buy them in the market, on a stall in the market. And - o
f
 course each one were given a glass of wine, you see, to drink the health of the baby, and - little - between the sips of the wine and eating the packet of this black and red jelly babies, I became very sick. And I can remember sick all over the lovely wh
