\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5506367 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 Did you treat your brother like an employer in the shop?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7226846 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 No. No. I felt it was my parents, because really they kept a share in really - for us - for the girls so}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4272343\charrsid2636949  that - we could feel that we we}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 re independent then you see. When Idris got married he - but when he had a son my mother turned that share over }{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4272343\charrsid2636949 thinking - the son}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949  would be interested in the business, but of course he wasn't, he went in for something else.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5506367 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 How did you feel about the work, well you have been talking about it now?
