Yes, these young men I tell you that used to come to the shop, they'd be - come in little groups you see, these boys would, and - we'd go to the various - not - some belonging to other churches and 
other - another choir and we'd go with them, always in groups.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5506367 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 Always in groups, you wouldn't go with just one?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7226846 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 No. No. Not until I went seriously with my own husband. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5506367 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 Was there any significance in that do you think?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7226846 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 Oh yes. You
 could sum up the character I think - of the boys, when you mixed with them like that you see, so - we mixed with so many in the shop, all types, a}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11236177\charrsid2636949 nd with so many in the operatic}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949  society and drama, and that's where you found out what type of character he was, I think. I think it - it strengthened you and made you stronger in forming your opinion about a man.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5506367 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 Would you go out at all on your own with a boy then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7226846 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 Oh yes. Once or twice. Once or twice and if you didn't like him well you drop him of course.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5506367 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 Where would you go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7226846 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 
Oh the walk then was up the Hospital Road, you know, as we call it. Up the mountain and - down the beach, up Dyffryn Valley, you see. Those were the walks in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5506367 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 Did your parents meet your friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7226846 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 Oh
 yes, yes, yes, oh - and we used to have a lot of little - musical evenings here because we were so musical and these friends would come in, some of them were - had very good voices, belonged to make voice choirs and that. Well they'd come in and we'd hav
e a wonderful time you know in our front room with the musical side of it. There was very - very fond of painting and things like that at that time and fancy work. Yes, I was too, pen painting.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5506367 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 You used to have sketching didn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7226846 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 Exactly. And 
