\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7226846 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 
Well of course the girls were out - each one were out at a job, the father - the mother at home of course looking after the house and the fathe
r was a boss in a - in a cotton mill up there. And - but - very musical. Very very musical, all of them were musical, they could all play instruments.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5506367 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 Was it the same sort of house as you lived in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7226846 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 No, it was a three storey house. Yes, it was very - very high house. In a place called Bluebell Hill. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5506367 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 And his father's occupation?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7226846 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 He had a - he was a boss in a - in a cotton mill.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5506367 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 Was he brought up to go to church or chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7226846 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 Oh yes, yes, he was a - there was a church and th
en - and the sisters were - one of them used to go to - the - was the Methodist in the Albert Hall, it was a treat to go to the Albert Hall on a Sunday night. Packed, four thousand people. They had four organists, and I can remember the - the - main organ
i
st was a great composer, but it was the second I liked best, he was a - had a - a very tasteful way of playing the organ, it was a terrific - Jessie Booth - Boots cash chemist presented the organ, when he gave it it was twenty-five thousand then, but - wh
at it would cost today I don't know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5506367 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 Was that the chapel that Wally went to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7226846 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 Yes. To the Wesleyan - the - it was in the Albert Hall, Nottingham.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5506367 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 Did you often visit his parents after that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7226846 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 Oh yes. We used to go there every year, spend our holiday there, for a fortnight. And I'd go for weekends in between.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5506367 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 Before you were married did you go up often?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7226846 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 Oh yes, yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5506367 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 As time went on were you treated as one of the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7226846 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5506367 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 Not always as a guest?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7226846 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 Oh
 no, no, they thought the world of me. They weren't too - they weren't like the Welsh - they weren't - I can't - his mother was - oh she was a - a very pretty woman his mother was, beauty - two of the most beautiful blue yes I think I've ever seen with an
y
body, small short little woman. But the father was very - Wally was like his father, he was - and he had a beard. And the sisters were - they weren't as - affectionate as the Welsh people, not as warm. You know. But they thought - oh they thought the worl
d of me, they were - I - I was - very very welcome.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5506367 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 You became one of the family now?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7226846 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5506367 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 Not a guest?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7226846 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 Oh dear no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5506367 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 Did they let you and Wally talk together by yourselves?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7226846 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 Oh yes. Yes. Oh yes, yes, we -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5506367 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 For how long you know and when?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7226846 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 Oh - go in the - in the - we'd go into the - their front room, we'd have a little tune on the piano and - that sort of things you see.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5506367 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 How did you get on with your parents in law after you were married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7226846 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 My people in law
? Oh fine. Just the same. To the end. And I can remember the last time I saw my father-in-law, he was - for a man that was so very autocratic in his manner, you know, and - had been so down on the Welsh, thanked me for the wonderful wife I'd made for my h
usband, and thanking my mother for the wonderful way she treated him and had given him such welcome and - and that's the last time I saw him. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5506367 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 When would you see them after you were married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7226846 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 Oh - still kept on going on holidays there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5506367 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 Would you help them with any odd jobs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7226846 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 
They wouldn't allow me to, I - I would - I used to like to dust around and we'd go and do the shopping. We'd go out to Nottingham, we'd always bring something - special back for a nice meal you know or - we'd - br
ing chicken or some - lovely shops up at Nottingham, was a marvel}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7537729\charrsid2636949 l}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 
ous place for shopping, very clean city, a lovely city altogether. Of course it was, such a beautiful city you see. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5506367 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 What did you call them before marriage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7226846 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 Oh ma and pa I'd call - Wally's father and - oh - or -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5506367 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 Before you were married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7226846 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 Oh Mr and Mrs Whitelam I'd say, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5506367 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 After marriage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7226846 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 Oh yes, ma and pa we'd call them afterwards, I called them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5506367 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 Can you remember the first time that he met your parents?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7226846 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 
Yes. It was the time my father was very dead against me going with him you see, and - my sister - was very popular at that time taking the lead in the operatic society, my young sister was going with a - an hoteliers son, in Port Talbot,
 managing the Grand Hotel, and my father got to hear of this, disgusted, what was happening to the two younger daughters, he said, the roof's going to - so one Thursday now my mother wasn't having peace with my father, that I'd have to - do away with Wall
y
, that would have to stop you see. So we'd go every Thursday afternoon, because he was playing in the night you see, so Thursday afternoon, a half day in the shop and we'd always go for our walk - round Pennacar, down to Carmarthen Road and - different ro
u
tes every week you know. And - I told - and we were going out to tea to my brother Will's young lady then, Gertie, who's his wife now, lived in Carlana, and we were going out to her mother's to tea, then we went round Pennacar and down where that pond use
d to be where the ti}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7537729\charrsid2636949 n works is in Carmarthen, then }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 
crossing that bridge across the Avon river, to go to Gertie's house, so - it was down there that I told him now that I'm afraid it would have to stop. And he asked why. And I said my father didn't like the 
idea that I was going with a musician that - more of a showman than anything else, he didn't like one of his daughters going with one of them, and that - of course I said there was a young minister, a young student who was very - very very keen on me at t
h
e time and of course - Deacon's son, I mean this as it should be with my father. So - he knew this man was very sweet, this young man, he was writing continuously to me these letters. Well it had to stop. Well I - I told him there, he said, no, he said, i
t
's not going to stop, I'm not giving you up. I'm coming to see your parents tomorrow. And I'm going to tell them I've come from as good a home and family as you have, from a very good family too, his father's family were from the higher - the Morley peopl
e
, and - he had an uncle, a big man he was his uncle, Sir John Morley in - in the - Steel in Nottingham knocking us in a - in a hat, he - they were from a very - his father was from a very good family, and - he said, I've come from quite equally as good a 
f
amily as you have and I'm coming to see your father tomorrow. And he did. He said - if it wasn't me there was to be nobody else, but he was determined it was to be Gwen or no one, whether they liked it or no, and that he was a - from as good a family and 
he was quite a good character and there would be nobody else in his life and I think I said my father - he - he made a very big impression on father that day, and - that he dismissed the idea altogether.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5506367 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 What did you feel like?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7226846 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 I felt terrible. I
 felt terrible. I didn't - well when I came and said to my mother, I said, he's coming to see daddy and you tomorrow. What for, she said. Well I don't want to be - well she said, you'd better had, he - he's that t}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7537729\charrsid2636949 y}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 pe of man I said, he won't take no for an answer. I said he'll be hammering this door tomorrow so you can get yourself ready.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5506367 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 You were in the shop were you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7226846 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 I was in the shop, oh I - oh I couldn't have stood it. Oh no. I wouldn't come near So he waited 'til my father came home from work
, so that he could have - could have his lunch and came at the appropriate time and of course he said his piece and - my mother of course - always liked him, and she could see what type of character he was 'cos my father hadn't come in contact with him at
 all.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5506367 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 Your father hadn't met him before?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7226846 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 No, he hadn't met him, not to speak to personally.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5506367 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 So what did your father think?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7226846 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 Oh well, to his die - to his dying day he said what a wonderful pair we were, me and my brother in law.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5506367 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 Did Mr Whitelam often visit your parents after that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7226846 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 Oh yes. Yes, he'd come and - and I use to buy - he was in lodgings of course and I'd buy his - meat, I'd buy his weekend meat you see.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5506367 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 He was only in lodgings about a hundred or two hundred yards away?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7226846 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 That's right. Very short distance. Oh yes, he'd call often. Call often to see them you know and - and - and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5506367 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 He used to feed himself did he when he was in lodgings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7226846 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 Yes, he'd buy his own food, that's how it was then. Then I'd buy 
his joint, the weekend joint you see, we'd call here every Saturday night and have his supper her on Saturday night, before he'd go home - from -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5506367 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 Just the once he'd come in the week?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7226846 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 In the week. No, no. No, no, no., not in the week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5506367 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 Was this the first boy you ever brought home for them to meet?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7226846 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 
No. There was a - several boys, but there was one also very - did you remember Jack - Will Cook? Great friend of my brother Bryn, he rose to a very high position - in London after, brilliant fe
llow he was. And Gwyn Thomas, he became a headmaster and still after that, and Bryn Singleton, wonderful pianist, you remember Bryn Singleton, Jack - Smith, now they'd all come here - oh, they were here nearly every night, those boys, crowd of boys. And -

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5506367 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 But not Wally?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7226846 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 
No. No. But these boys would be playing cards in the front room, Bryn - and my brothers were very great sticklers who you were going with. Very particular. I think boys were very sensitive about their sisters, they wanted them to
 have the best. Well this Will Cook he was very very sweet on me. But - I didn't like his - character at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5506367 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 Those boys were coming home because they were with your brothers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7226846 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 Yes. Music.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5506367 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 Was there any boy you bro}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7537729\charrsid2636949 u}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 ght home yourself to meet your parents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7226846 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 Yes, there was a young fellow who was in business - when I was in the shop he was in Leonard}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7537729\charrsid2636949 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 s boot shop opposite, a - a young fellow called - Bill Mehuish you see, brought him home. He was a very nice young man, he - then of course - h
e went from here to another shop and I - I - I'd - I - I wasn't very keen. He wasn't a church worker and that sort of thing you know. So I dropped him. Oh - there were a lot of boys in our life you know, we were very - we were very pop - being in the chap
el of course we - and being an outfitters shop of course we - we - of course, we - we were very popular. And in these different societies in the town you see. Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5506367 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 Did your parents warn you off certain boys, or encourage you to go with any others?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7226846 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 
They were - no, they didn't mind as long as he had a good character, he had to be a young man of good character. They weren't - and the character was the main thing. And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5506367 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 Now how did they mean character?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7226846 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 Morally good. Gentleman. Yes, she - they liked them being -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5506367 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 What about if they didn't go to chapel or church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7226846 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 
Well my father didn't like that very well, he said, no, no, no, my mother wasn't very keen either but of course we encouraged them to come with us you see. Now - that's
 how Blod went to Beth any with her - with her young man, Billie Phillips, because of course she couldn't follow the Welsh and I could - and that's how I went a member - I didn't go a member to Bethany but my husband became a member of Bethany, and I'd go
 with him on Sunday night, you see, and go to all the other services, to the Welsh morning in Dyffryn.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5506367 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 After you married you remained a member in your own chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7226846 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 Oh yes, I still remain.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5506367 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 And went there in the morning and Sunday school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7226846 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 That's right.
