\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5506367 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 What about clothes, trousseau, special clothes?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7226846 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 Yes, you'd - you'd - you'd - make your underclothing, you see, for under the coat - outer clothes would go - y
ou'd go buy according to style, you wouldn't have you wouldn't buy those - in excess before you were married, only the underwear. That's right. After.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5506367 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 Would you have underwear in your bottom drawer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7226846 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 Oh yes. Oh yes, a good stock of underwear, eve
rything like that, because - that didn't change very much at that time. Today we've had a big change, in the nylon and that you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5506367 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 Would you make the underwear a long time before you married, before you were engaged or after you were engaged?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7226846 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 No, after we were engaged. Tassel silk was very fashionable in those days. And we'd make a lot of - underwear out of }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16669188\charrsid2636949 tussah}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949  and crepe de chine was a very big thing. Nightdresses of crepe de chine and that you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5506367 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 Who did you first see to arrange about the wedding?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7226846 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 
Oh - first of all our minister, you see. You'd have a - fix the date then if it was possible for him to be there, the time, but of course as I tell you I had to go very quietly on a Sunday with my brother - my brother being so critical
ly ill, we had to bring it from a fussy wedding to - to - but still a white wedding mind on a Sunday morning at half past nine in the Holy Cross church, whereas I'd have married in my own Dyffryn Presbyterian church in the ordinary way you see. And then -

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5506367 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 You went to church to marry quieter?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7226846 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 Quieter. By taxi of course then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5506367 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 How long before the wedding would you have to arrange about it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7226846 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 Oh - that's right, oh you'd have to go about six weeks before. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5506367 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 Was there any particular reason for the wedding date you chose?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7226846 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 July because we thought it was a good month, and that's when my husband was having his holidays. That's when we went.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5506367 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 You have really mentioned why you picked a particular building?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7226846 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5506367 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 You didn't marry in the chapel you went to?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7226846 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 No. In - it was half past}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16669188\charrsid2636949  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 nine in the Sunday morning, between the services, the communion service and the church service at eleven. And we only had one taxi because my brother couldn't stand - the noise of a motor c
ar, he was in the front bedroom, his - he'd gone - his nerves were - were so weak he couldn't stand, and the rest of - we had to curtail it, just a - and they all walked up 'cost it isn't very far as you know. Not to make a fuss you see. And Doctor Philip
s
 was here when we came back, because - and my brother - wore silk pyjamas - and white heather - Idris my brother took his place as best man, and - white heather - he wore his white heather on his silk pyjamas and he cut the cake in the bedroom. Doctor Phi
l
ips came to inject him you see. But he broke down when he saw my husband when he shook hands with him because he was looking forward - he was beginning to learn the cello with my brother and he was very fond of music, this brother that was dying, fond of 
the cello.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5506367 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 Why did you choose a religious ceremony?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7226846 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 
Oh because we'd been brought up I believe. I believe it's something far more lasting, something more eternal somehow - about it a religious sermon - service. Oh yes, definitely a religious service.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5506367 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 Did you have any difficulty in getting your parents agreement?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7226846 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 
No, none at all. Once they knew my husband, and handled him and saw he was a very fine man that he'd - take every care of me they were very - very pleased.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5506367 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 Had you wanted a large or a small wedding?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7226846 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 
Well we had prepared for a fussy wedding, and my sister Blod was a bridesmaid, she was still the bridesmaid that day, you see, and my father going in his morning suit and I can remember - one of our neighbours Miss Kent who 
lived the other side of the road, watching my father going out and she thought he looked a picture, he looked like Lloyd George. He had a moustache. And he wasn't unlike him. And he - he always went in his morning coat to our weddings and his cuffs and hi
s - striped trousers you see, yes. Oh it was quite a - a nice - service but very quiet because of my brother being so ill, he couldn't stand a fuss.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5506367 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 How did you decide who to inv}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16669188\charrsid2636949 i}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 te?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7226846 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 Well - we - now then, my brother who was - very ill, his girl f
riend, he was engaged to her, she was here. Some friends of ours, some relatives, but then - we would have had a very big fussy wedding in the ordinary way, they would all come that one day - but we couldn't have a big reception because of my brother bein
g
 so ill. So - we spread it out in days, my mother's sisters, my father's sisters, that, you see, had - we - we had different days after that - here, in the house, and gave a - after we were married, but the morning we were married, mind we had lots of fri
ends, we had cousins, some cousins here, they all came here, but we kept it so much quieter than it should have been.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5506367 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 You don't remember how many were there on either side?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7226846 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 Oh and I tell you the exciting part about it. When we came out of the ch
urch, much to our surprise we belonged to the - Port Talbot operatic society and my}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16669188\charrsid2636949  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 
sister was in the lead and she looked lovely in mauve - and a white fox fur and I remember she had a grey hat with lavender covering - I was in white - covering over the br
im of the hat, she did look - she was a very pretty girl. The whole operatic society when we came out were outside, it was with streamers across the - the - the out - the exist - the exit and entrance to the church, you know Holy Cross church, with ribbon
s across, paper ribbons. The whole society turned out. On the Sunday morning.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5506367 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 What about the guests at the wedding, do you remember how many there were on both sides?
