only about five when she was married and I'd be about nine or ten, and just after we came over here to live, and - oh and he was in his grey long coat and his top hat and a whip with a white bow, horses with white ears. Two horses, in this - and going dow
n
, and then you know the Prudrith Bridge there'd be men across there with a rope and we weren't allowed to pass 'til we threw money out to these people. Same on the way back from the church you see. She had broughams. You know, where they - were horses on 
it, oh it was very stylish. Very stylish that was.
