\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7226846 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 Well I was in the shop of course - and everybody was coming in and the girls from - in the shops were com
ing in, and wishing me all the best, bringing me little gifts. All the Moffats, the florists girls, 'cos - they - they were - they always make - my sister used to have lots of bouquets - on the last night of a show in the operatic, and of course they were
 very friendly with us, and they'd call us in to see these bouquets before they would be taken to the theatre, the different people had - we weren't supposed to know they were going to be given you see, showing me now. Oh yes, and oh yes, everybody - \{
BLANK\}
 Oh yes, and the boys - they made your life - agony for the last week before you were getting married telling you terrible things - to upset you see, to put you right off. And I was rather a sensitive modest - modest person, it scared the life out of me. 
Yes, it did really. Oh the thought of going to - sleep with a man, they were telling me shocking things. Oh, oh, they were dreadful. I was really scared stiff when I got married.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5506367 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13726020\charrsid2636949 Of course you were in a mans outfitting shop?
