,
 and the relatives, it was a big thing with her to open the door - where there was a - a funeral in the street. And I never saw anyone else do that before - nor after. And she'd dress as if she was going to the funeral, and stand and - of course it used t
o
 be singing by the door years ago, you see, the - the choir or church party if there was a choir or the people in the funeral, because they were large funerals then, and - she'd join in the singing. Always in her best clothes, black hat and black coat, fo
r a mark of respect.
